.TH "fm10k_iov_configure_tc_pf" 9 "fm10k_iov_configure_tc_pf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fm10k_iov_configure_tc_pf \- Configure the shaping group for VF
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "s32" fm10k_iov_configure_tc_pf
.BI "(struct fm10k_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "u16 vf_idx "  ","
.BI "int rate "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
pointer to the HW structure
.IP "vf_idx" 12
index of VF receiving GLORT
.IP "rate" 12
Rate indicated in Mb/s

Configured the TC for a given VF to allow only up to a given number
of Mb/s of outgoing Tx throughput.
